Package: equil2
Title: Calculate Urinary Saturation with the EQUIL2 Algorithm
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Bill", "Denney", email="wdenney@humanpredictions.com", role=c("aut", "cre"), comment=c(ORCID="0000-0002-5759-428X"))
Description: Calculate saturation of ionic substances in urine based on sodium,
  potassium, calcium, magnesium, ammonia, chloride, phosphate, sulfate,
  oxalate, citrate, ph, and urate.  This program is intended for research use,
  only.  The code within is translated from EQUIL2 Visual Basic code based on
  Werness, et al 1985 to R.  The Visual Basic code was kindly provided by Dr.
  John Lieske of the Mayo Clinic.
Imports:
    units
